  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. However, multiple mitigating factors are present: this is a first-time offense, the crime was non-violent, and the defendant has already demonstrated accountability by partially repaying the stolen funds. The spectator's outburst suggesting a 10-year sentence is wholly disproportionate to the severity of this white-collar crime. A short period of incarceration is appropriate to emphasize the seriousness of the breach of trust, followed by probation to ensure the defendant can work and fully compensate the victim.",
